BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:wC0gdMaZaM7ZQPKwBYi4m
SUMMARY:Silent Book Club Night!!
DTSTAMP:20260403T051049Z
DTSTART:20260409T013000Z
DESCRIPTION:Welcome to Capitol Hill's Silent Book Club! We meet twice a mon
	th at a different restaurant or coffee shop around Capitol Hill to show su
	pport to our wonderful community!\n\nWe aren't your typical book club.\n\n
	There is no assigned reading and you're welcome to use any medium to enjoy
	 your story \\(i.e. paperback\, audiobook\, kindle\, etc.\\). This is a ju
	dgement free zone. If you're into fiction\, non-fiction\, or graphic novel
	s\, bring whatever you enjoy!\n\nOur mission is to create a welcoming envi
	ronment for a diverse group to share their love of books while supporting 
	local businesses in the process. Whether you're a bookworm or just looking
	 for a relaxing night out\, this event is perfect for anyone who wants to 
	be a part of our bookish community.\n\nHow it works:\n\n6:30 PM - Get sett
	led\, order food/drinks\, meet fellow book lovers\n\n7:00 PM - Read whatev
	er book you like in your preferred platform\n\n8:00 PM - Socialize\, keep 
	reading\, or pay your bill and enjoy the rest of your night\n\n9:00 PM - Q
	uinn's Pub closes\n\nCome alone or bring a friend. Don't miss out on this 
	unique experience!\n\nFollow us on Instagram to stay up to date on our upc
	oming events: @silentbookclubcapitolhill.\n\n\\*\\*\\*This is a free event
	 but to show our appreciation to Quinn's\, a purchase is required.\n\nhttp
	s://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/silent-book-club-night/18475003/
	2026-04-08T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/silent-book-club-night/18
	475003/2026-04-08T00
LOCATION:Quinn's Pub\, 1001 East Pike Street\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gPSVHD7Fkier8cVy6XGD6
SUMMARY:My Dinner with SAM
DTSTAMP:20260403T051049Z
DTSTART:20260409T013000Z
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the art of food at intimate chef dinners inspired by 
	SAM's three unique sites. Dine in artful and inspiring settings while enjo
	ying a dynamic evening with culinary artists\, local producers and makers\
	, and more. Stay tuned\, tickets to these limited-seating dinners will be 
	available in January. Dinner dates and venues Thursday\, March 12 6:30 pm 
	Guest chef: Preeti Agarwal\, Meesha and Kricket Club Seattle Asian Art Mus
	eum Wednesday\, April 8 6:30 pm Guest chef: Kevin Smith\, Beast & Cleaver\
	, Little Beast\, and The Peasant Seattle Art Museum May Olympic Sculpture 
	Park Guest chef & date to come My Dinner with SAM is a major fundraising e
	vent and all proceeds benefit SAM's education\, community engagement\, and
	 exhibition programs. 3-Dinner Series VIP Tickets $1\,250 per person One V
	IP ticket to each dinner Recognition as a series sponsor on all evening pr
	ograms and dedicated event emails Special take-away at each dinner Complim
	entary parking at Seattle Art Museum and Olympic Sculpture Park Individual
	 Dinner Tickets Benefactor - $550 per person One ticket to one dinner Reco
	gnition on evening program Special take-away at the dinner Complimentary p
	arking at Seattle Art Museum and Olympic Sculpture Park Patron - $350 per 
	person One ticket to one dinner All but $150 per dinner is tax-deductible.
	 If you are unable to attend the event\, please consider making a donation
	 to support My Dinner with SAM. To make a tax-deductible donation\, please
	 contact us at dinnerwithSAM@seattleartmuseum.org or 206.654.3123.\n\nhttp
	s://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/my-dinner-with-sam/17799815/2026
	-04-08T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/my-dinner-with-sam/177998
	15/2026-04-08T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H30M
END:VEVENT
